Hello All! We are currently seeking 11 people to cast for a project featuring the internet sensation Sturniolo Triplets! We prefer individuals (Male) who have a similar stature to the triplets, around 5'8 ", slim, and 18 years or older, though applicants of any ethnicity are welcome.

The shoot is scheduled for Monday from 11 AM to 4 PM in West Hollywood. Although this gig is unpaid, it offers a valuable opportunity to be featured in a high-profile video, and food will be provided.

If anyone is interested, please let me know. They can contact me at campbellchae@gmail.com. Thank you!

topComments.text: Very much interested

üé¨ The Foundry Acting Studio‚Ä¶. Where Real Actors Are Made

Have you ever wanted to be an actor, but people told you it was impossible?
Maybe they laughed. Maybe they said, ‚ÄúYeah right, you‚Äôll be on TV one day.‚Äù
Maybe you believed them.

The truth is, it is possible. And we‚Äôre proving it every single day.

At The Foundry Acting Studio, we‚Äôve taken people from call centres, factories, construction sites and put them on real film sets. We‚Äôve helped ordinary people create extraordinary careers.

Because when you train with us, you‚Äôre not just joining another acting class, you‚Äôre stepping into a professional studio that‚Äôs already earned the highest recognition possible:

‚ú® SPOTLIGHT APPROVED ‚Äì our curriculum exceeds the UK‚Äôs highest acting standard by over three times.
üåç SAG RECOGNISED ‚Äì the same union that represents every Hollywood star on earth.
üé• FILM-FOCUSED TRAINING ‚Äì you don‚Äôt just practice scenes; you act in real films. Short films, features, festival submissions, full productions we make them all in-house, to professional industry standard.

And all of this ‚Äî for just ¬£100 every 4 weeks (¬£80 for teens).
No false promises. No city centre price tags. Just real, legitimate training and real results.

We believe acting shouldn‚Äôt be locked behind London doors.
That‚Äôs why we‚Äôre bringing professional-level training to Yorkshire and the North, so anyone with the passion to perform can do it, whether you‚Äôre 16 or 60, starting fresh or chasing the dream you left behind.

üé≠ Because the truth is: there is no other independent studio in the UK that offers what we do.
We‚Äôre Spotlight approved.
We‚Äôre SAG recognised.
We make films.
We get results.

You don‚Äôt get more legitimate than that.
You just don‚Äôt.

So, if you‚Äôre ready to stop wondering ‚Äúwhat if‚Äù and start actually doing it, this is your moment.

üî• SPOTLIGHT APPROVED. SAG RECOGNISED. FILM FOCUSED.
The Foundry Acting Studio‚Ä¶.
Where impossible dreams get rehearsed, filmed, and released.

üé¨ Adult & Teen Classes | üé≠ Limited Places | üåç Open Across Yorkshire & The North

sharedPost.text:
Statister s√∏ges til kortfilmen "KLAGESANG"  (ul√∏nnet)

Hej alle sammen,

Vi er i gang med en ny kortfilm, KLAGESANG, en afgangsfilm af 18 Frames, og vi leder efter statister til nogle smukke og stemningsfulde middelalderscener i Helsing√∏r.

Vi s√∏ger:

Nonner
Torsdag d. 23. oktober
Fredag d. 24. oktober

Riddere
Torsdag d. 23. oktober

Det hele bliver optaget i dagstimerne.

Om filmen:

Klagesang er en coming-of-age kortfilm inspireret af Hildegard von Bingens liv ‚Äì en sanselig og spirituel oplysningsrejse midt i middelalderens religi√∏se m√∏rke.

Vi f√∏lger den unge nonne Hilde, der f√•r visioner gennem naturen, som hendes abbedisse tolker som guddommelige.

Da den s√•rede Abbas ‚Äì en persisk mand p√• flugt fra korsfarerne ‚Äì s√∏ger tilflugt i klostret, bliver Hildes tro sat p√• pr√∏ve, og en ny form for spiritualitet begynder at spire.

Filmen er ikke anti-religi√∏s, men handler om tro, tvivl og menneskelighed ‚Äì og om at finde sin egen vej i m√∏det med en verden i forandring.

Optagelserne foreg√•r i Helsing√∏r

Hvis du (eller nogen du kender) kunne have lyst til at v√¶re med i et sp√¶ndende og meningsfuldt filmprojekt, s√• skriv endelig til mig

Enten her p√• Facebook eller p√• mail: livannettemuus@outlook.dk

L√¶s mere om 18 frames her: https://www.18frames.dk/

Saturday, November 8, 2025
Greenwood Oasis Theater ‚Äì 7621 S. Greenwood Ave, Chicago, IL
Showtime: 7 PM | VIP Experience: 4 PM | Doors Open: 6 PM
FREE PARKING

Come dressed in your best 40s, 50s, 60s, or 70s attire!
(It‚Äôs recommended ‚Äî not required ‚Äî for the full experience!)

Step back in time and experience a powerful musical journey through the Great Migration, Bronzeville‚Äôs rich Black history, and the soul of World War II-era Chicago ‚Äî told through acting, singing, dancing, and narration.

 Featuring unforgettable portrayals of:
Billie Holiday, Nat King Cole, Ella Fitzgerald, Dinah Washington, Cab Calloway, Etta James
Plus a moving tribute to Minnie Riperton, Chicago‚Äôs own.

A dynamic cast. Real stories. Legendary music.
This is more than entertainment ‚Äî it‚Äôs edutainment.

Group rates (10+) already discounted online

items.text:
PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS ‚Äî NOW SEEKING FINAL CREW MEMBERS

**We‚Äôre bringing a few more people aboard an already full production team for George Orwell‚Äôs *****1984*****, directed by M.A.C.**

We‚Äôre looking for:
* **Assistant Producer**
* **Social Media / Marketing** Manager
* **Sound Board Operator**
* **Lighting Board Operator**

Performances run **December 4‚Äì7, 2025** at **Three Stories Theater (937 Liberty Ave, Downtown Pittsburgh)**.

Our **cast and crew of over 30 artists** are already deep in rehearsals and production work, and our design team has fully built out the world of the show. We‚Äôre looking for a few final team members to join the effort and help bring this ambitious production to completion.

**ASSISTANT PRODUCER**

Supports the Executive Producer with logistics, communications, scheduling, and coordination across departments. Ideal for someone organized, proactive, and interested in hands-on producing experience in a professional theatre environment.

**SOCIAL MEDIA / MARKETING MANAGER**

Join our marketing team to help manage social channels, coordinate content posting, and support our show rollout.
We already have **two resident photographers/videographers** and a **backlog of content ready to be edited, polished, and posted**. You‚Äôll be shaping how this production is presented to the public.

SOUND & LIGHTING BOARD OPERATORS

We have professional **sound and lighting designers** who have already built out the show‚Äôs systems and cues ‚Äî we‚Äôre simply looking for **two operators** to put that design work into action during **tech week and performances**.
Experience with QLab (for Sound) or ETC lighting consoles (for Lighting) is helpful, but a good sense of focus and teamwork is most important.

**COMPENSATION TYPE:** Volunteer / Possible post-show stipend
*(We want to be transparent: these are volunteer positions, but if funds allow, a small stipend may be available after the production.) *

**DATES & COMMITMENTS:**
* **Rehearsals (for reference):** Sundays, 6‚Äì9 PM starting August 3, 2025
Trust Arts Education Center ‚Äî 807 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA
* **Tech Week:** November 24 ‚Äì December 3, 2025 (dark day on Thanksgiving)
* **Performances:** December 4‚Äì7, 2025 (5 performances total)
Three Stories Theater ‚Äî 937 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA

We‚Äôre happy to work with your schedule ‚Äî please share any known conflicts when reaching out.

**TO APPLY**
Please email **playboxpgh@gmail.com** with:
* Resume (or a brief note on your experience and interest)
* Availability during tech week and performances

If it seems like a good fit, we‚Äôll be in touch right away!

Thank you,
Marc Palombo
**PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS**

Hello!

My name is Marc and I am currently an MFA in Cinematic Arts student at Concordia.

I‚Äôm putting out a very early casting call for my thesis short film ***Reprendre***. Production is planned for **summer 2026 (Exact Dates TBD)**.

This is a **paid role**, open to both union and non union actors. Whether you‚Äôre a professional or a first time actor, you‚Äôre welcome to audition. If you don't reside in Montreal, transportation, lodging, and food will be paid.

The posters include all the key details for your reference.

I‚Äôm especially interested in talent with piano skills, though this is **not mandatory**. While the film involves piano, its heart centers on intergenerational trauma, masculinity, and healing.

Please feel free to email me if you have any questions or concerns!

items.text:
Title: Forever Home

Genre: Horror/Thriller

Logline: A young couple tours their dream home with an unsettling real estate agent, only to discover the house holds a dark secret.

Roles:

-Raymond Russo

Age: 45-60

Gender: Male

Ethnicity: White

Description: A veteran real estate agent with a polished exterior. He is charming, articulate, and seemingly trustworthy. Beneath the polished exterior, however, is something deeply unsettling.

Requirements: Actor must be skilled with subtle menace and controlled delivery. Suited look; sharp features a plus.

-Susan

Age: 25-35

Gender: Female

Ethnicity: Any

Description: An optimistic, curious young woman who‚Äôs excited about starting a new chapter with her husband. She‚Äôs practical yet impulsive when her curiosity is piqued.

Requirements: Needs range from natural warmth to terror. Must handle emotional intensity and physical acting in horror scenes.

Production Type: Indie

Contact Information: [luke@lostefilms.com](mailto:luke@lostefilms.com)

Run Time: Short

Compensation: Paid

Union Status: Non-union

Audition Information: Please email headshot, resume and demo reel to email provided (luke@lostefilms.com). We will send a copy of the script and audition instructions.

Shooting Schedule: One short shoot day must happen as soon as possible to capture the brief exterior scenes before leaves are all gone. The other full shoot day will be scheduled close to the exterior shoot day.

Filming Location: Denver metro area

Looking forward to your submissions!

CU DENVER STUDENT FILM CASTING CALL

Title: *Mannequins*

Genre: Thriller/Horror

Written and Directed by Archer Beck

Produced by Owen Etter

Logline: In a world where otherworldly invaders have forced humanity to live out a sitcom for their entertainment, the daughter figure in a mismatched family of strangers attempts to escape from her lifelong suburban prison.

Synopsis: In a carefully manufactured sitcom world, Daughter begins to see cracks in the illusion of her perfect family life. While she dreams of escaping the endless loop of canned laughter and staged dinners, Father insists they obey their unseen creators and preserve the family‚Äôs image at all costs. Their clash escalates into open rebellion‚Äîuntil Mother, torn between them, helps Daughter break free. Outside the safety of their household, however, Daughter discovers a world ruled by an even stranger, otherworldly power‚Äîand must decide whether freedom is worth the price of losing the only family she‚Äôs ever known.

Main Roles: 

**Daughter **(16-18): Eldest daughter figure who is hellbent on escaping and finding answers.

**Father **(40s): Head of the household who is trying to keep the family unit obedient to the alien conquerors that control them.

**Mother **(40s): Silent caretaker of the family.

**Son **(8-10): Golden child of the household.

Union Status: Non-Union

Production Type: Student Short Film

Runtime: 10-12 minutes

Compensation: Meals Provided, Any Transportation Fees Paid For, Film & IMDb Credit, Copy of Final Cut

Location: Denver Area

Submission Details:

To submit for audition, please send headshot(s), resum√©, and reel (if available) to owen.etter@ucdenver.edu.

Logline: In a world where otherworldly invaders have forced humanity to live out a sitcom for their entertainment, the daughter figure in a mismatched family of strangers attempts to escape from her lifelong suburban prison.

Synopsis: In a carefully manufactured sitcom world, Daughter begins to see cracks in the illusion of her perfect family life. While she dreams of escaping the endless loop of canned laughter and staged dinners, Father insists they obey their unseen creators and preserve the family‚Äôs image at all costs. Their clash escalates into open rebellion‚Äîuntil Mother, torn between them, helps Daughter break free. Outside the safety of their household, however, Daughter discovers a world ruled by an even stranger, otherworldly power‚Äîand must decide whether freedom is worth the price of losing the only family she‚Äôs ever known.

Main Roles: 

**Daughter **(16-18): Eldest daughter figure who is hellbent on escaping and finding answers.

**Father **(40s): Head of the household who is trying to keep the family unit obedient to the alien conquerors that control them.

**Mother **(40s): Silent caretaker of the family.

**Son **(8-10): Golden child of the household.

Union Status: Non-Union

Production Type: Student Short Film

Runtime: 10-12 minutes

Compensation: Meals Provided, Any Transportation Fees Paid For, Film & IMDb Credit, Copy of Final Cut

Location: Denver Area

Submission Details:

To submit for audition, please send headshot(s), resum√©, and reel (if available) to owen.etter@ucdenver.edu.

Hi everyone! We‚Äôre filming a short home video‚Äìstyle flashback scene for our upcoming film Feel the Burn and are looking for a few performers to join us.

Roles:

 ‚Ä¢ Girl (ages 5‚Äì10) ‚Äì Caucasian

 ‚Ä¢ Boy (ages 5‚Äì10) ‚Äì Black / African Canadian

 ‚Ä¢ Mother (ages 30‚Äì40) ‚Äì Caucasian, preferably blonde, to play the girl‚Äôs mom

The scene will be shot to resemble nostalgic camcorder footage, capturing a warm and natural family moment.

Details:

 ‚Ä¢ Shoot Duration: Approximately 2 hours

 ‚Ä¢ Compensation: $75 per actor

 ‚Ä¢ Location: Metro Vancouver 

If you or someone you know fits the description and is interested, please send a recent photo and your contact info to feeltheburnmovie@gmail.com.

We welcome submissions from both professional and first-time performers!

The dates will be decided once we have a cast

The actual interview should take no more than one hour, plus setup and breakdown time

Bring your own camera and audio gear

Experience filming interviews is a plus

Professional and punctual

To Apply: Please send:

A link to your work/portfolio

Your contact information

Thank you, Joe

**DREAM. TEACH. INSPIRE. JOIN OUR BIRMINGHAM TEAM! üåü**

 

Dance&Arts is thrilled to be growing, and we're looking for passionate **teachers** to join our team right here in **Birmingham**! If you love inspiring young children (aged 4-16) through creative and performing arts, we want to hear from you!

 

We're seeking instructors for a variety of classes. Do you teach any of these styles?

 

‚úÖ **Dance (all styles)**

‚úÖ **Drama**

‚úÖ **Musical Theatre**

‚úÖ **Basic Gymnastics (mat-based only)**

‚úÖ **Arts & Crafts**

 

**üí∞ Great Pay:** We offer **¬£30 per hour**.

 

**IMPORTANT DBS REQUIREMENT**

Applicants must have a valid **Enhanced DBS**, or must be **willing to obtain one**. If you need to apply for one, **we will happily provide you with guidelines **for the process!

 

**üì© How to Apply:** Send your valid **Enhanced DBS and CV** to **admin@dancearts-uk.com**.

 

***Crucially, please include the position you are applying for and the location in the subject line of your email (e.g., Dance Teacher - Birmingham).***

 

Join us in bringing creativity, movement, and inspiration to the next generation in Birmingham!

 

We're also seeking instructors in **London, Nottingham, and Manchester**!

#JobOpportunity #BirminghamJobs #HiringTeachers #DanceAndArts #TeachingJobs #PerformingArts #CreativeEducation #Birmingham

‚ö°Ô∏èPAY WHAT YOU CAN showreel editing service‚ö°Ô∏è

Happy Friday all! 

I'm providing a showreel service for new or established actors/directors/cinematographers/comedians/hobbyists etc 

I'm an actor myself so I know how frustrating it can be, especially when you're starting out, to collate your footage together to get more work, without wanting to spend a fortune. 

Basically, send me your footage (or I can try and source it for you if it's commercially aired) and I shall edit it together into a lovely reel. Please see samples in the link below. 

As I'm wanting to add to my portfolio it will be PAY WHAT YOU CAN 

I'll look forward to hearing from you:
reelsforanyone@gmail.com 

Thanks!

items.text:
This is me (and Zoe), ten years into a journey that almost never started.

At 47, after a 16-year break, I tried to relaunch my acting career in Germany with no reel, no contacts, and very rusty skills. I had no idea how to explain the gap on my resume, and the thought of walking into a casting room again terrified me.

But giving up was not an option.

The solution hit me when I realized the problem itself was pointing the way forward. I needed training in English at a high level, and it did not exist in Munich. Flying to London, LA, or New York was unrealistic.

So I organized the workshops myself.

What happened next changed everything.

Instead of stumbling around in the dark trying to figure it out again, I could hit the ground running. Whenever I needed something like showreel material, headshots, the right kind of training, I organized it and got what I needed. If I had tried to piece it all together on my own, it would have taken ten times as long, and I did not have that kind of time.

That approach became my foundation. It is what eventually opened doors to work with studios like A24, Netflix, and Hallmark.

Along the way, I got world-class training for free as the organizer. A community of actors formed around those workshops. And unexpectedly, it also turned into steady income.

Here is the breakthrough: I always believed you had to "make it" before you could make money as a creative. What I discovered is that the journey itself can pay for itself.

Use what you need, whether that is training, practice, connections, or visibility, and shape it into something that lets other people get what they need too. That way you move your craft forward, build real relationships, get seen, and the process funds itself.

At first, I thought this only worked for actors because that is where I started. But the more I shared my story, the more I heard the same frustrations from other creatives: photographers, writers, artisans, even people into things like fermentation or traditional crafts. That's when it clicked. This approach is not just about acting. It can work anywhere someone is willing to use what they need to build what they want.

Ten years later, I am still living this way. I am constantly building skills, deepening connections, getting more visible in my craft, and funding it all as I go.

I am sharing this because I know too many people who keep their passions in the "someday" box. They wait until they feel "ready" or "expert enough" before letting themselves imagine it could actually support them.

But what if the very thing you think is holding you back is actually your starting point to a creative life that fits?

üëâ For me, it was not having reel material or training. What‚Äôs been that thing for you?

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of dog

topComments.text: The competitive nature of the wider job market really dictates that people choose talent over passion. When you are good at something, it is easier to become passionate about it. This is true for creative artists as much as anyone on any career path.

But giving up was not an option.

The solution hit me when I realized the problem itself was pointing the way forward. I needed training in English at a high level, and it did not exist in Munich. Flying to London, LA, or New York was unrealistic.

So I organized the workshops myself.

What happened next changed everything.

Instead of stumbling around in the dark trying to figure it out again, I could hit the ground running. Whenever I needed something like showreel material, headshots, the right kind of training, I organized it and got what I needed. If I had tried to piece it all together on my own, it would have taken ten times as long, and I did not have that kind of time.

That approach became my foundation. It is what eventually opened doors to work with studios like A24, Netflix, and Hallmark.

Along the way, I got world-class training for free as the organizer. A community of actors formed around those workshops. And unexpectedly, it also turned into steady income.

Here is the breakthrough: I always believed you had to "make it" before you could make money as a creative. What I discovered is that the journey itself can pay for itself.

Use what you need, whether that is training, practice, connections, or visibility, and shape it into something that lets other people get what they need too. That way you move your craft forward, build real relationships, get seen, and the process funds itself.

At first, I thought this only worked for actors because that is where I started. But the more I shared my story, the more I heard the same frustrations from other creatives: photographers, writers, artisans, even people into things like fermentation or traditional crafts. That's when it clicked. This approach is not just about acting. It can work anywhere someone is willing to use what they need to build what they want.

Ten years later, I am still living this way. I am constantly building skills, deepening connections, getting more visible in my craft, and funding it all as I go.

I am sharing this because I know too many people who keep their passions in the "someday" box. They wait until they feel "ready" or "expert enough" before letting themselves imagine it could actually support them.

But what if the very thing you think is holding you back is actually your starting point to a creative life that fits?

üëâ For me, it was not having reel material or training. What‚Äôs been that thing for you?
items.title: This is me (and Zoe), ten years into a journey that almost never started.

Does anyone know whether it is still possible for international students at the moment to get a film internship? I would be looking for Fall 2026 (I know it's in a long time but I prefer to prepare myself ahead), but when looking up at some of the internship opportunities, some of them state that they won't accept students with an F1/J1 visa (which used to work for interns too).

Then you can look no further than Marble Academy in Swinton, Manchester.

 

**Why Choose Marble Academy?**

Recognised by Spotlight as an academy of renowned excellence and winner of the **Manchester & North West Prestige Awards for**
**Drama School of the Year,** you'll receive authentic training from one of the best.
Our inspiring, award-winning tutor, Christian Le Feuvre, will help you unlock your potential, boost your confidence, help you improve the talent you have to get you where you want to
be in your career as an actor, and ultimately capture the attention of castingdirectors.

 

At Marble Academy, it‚Äôs not just about our classes; we create award-winning films, host workshops and provide casting opportunities for our students.

Explore our glowing reviews, learn about our
classes, and book your audition at: www.marbleacademy.co.uk.

 

**DON'T BE AN ACTOR BECAUSE YOU WANT TO;**
**BE AN ACTOR BECAUSE YOU 'HAVE' TO!**

items.text:
Have you ever wondered why some people simply fill the room the moment they walk in?
It‚Äôs not magic ‚Äî it‚Äôs presence. And it‚Äôs something you can actually train.
In this one-afternoon creative space, we explore presence and expression through psychological and theatre-based exercises. You‚Äôll learn how to connect more deeply with your body, attention, and authenticity ‚Äî whether you‚Äôre on stage, teaching, performing, or simply engaging with others in everyday life.

It‚Äôs not magic ‚Äî it‚Äôs presence. And it‚Äôs something you can actually train.
In this one-afternoon creative space, we explore presence and expression through psychological and theatre-based exercises. You‚Äôll learn how to connect more deeply with your body, attention, and authenticity ‚Äî whether you‚Äôre on stage, teaching, performing, or simply engaging with others in everyday life.

üé¨ The Foundry Acting Studio‚Ä¶. Where Real Actors Are Made

Have you ever wanted to be an actor, but people told you it was impossible?
Maybe they laughed. Maybe they said, ‚ÄúYeah right, you‚Äôll be on TV one day.‚Äù
Maybe you believed them.

The truth is, it is possible. And we‚Äôre proving it every single day.

At The Foundry Acting Studio, we‚Äôve taken people from call centres, factories, construction sites and put them on real film sets. We‚Äôve helped ordinary people create extraordinary careers.

Because when you train with us, you‚Äôre not just joining another acting class, you‚Äôre stepping into a professional studio that‚Äôs already earned the highest recognition possible:

‚ú® SPOTLIGHT APPROVED ‚Äì our curriculum exceeds the UK‚Äôs highest acting standard by over three times.
üåç SAG RECOGNISED ‚Äì the same union that represents every Hollywood star on earth.
üé• FILM-FOCUSED TRAINING ‚Äì you don‚Äôt just practice scenes; you act in real films. Short films, features, festival submissions, full productions we make them all in-house, to professional industry standard.

And all of this ‚Äî for just ¬£100 every 4 weeks (¬£80 for teens).
No false promises. No city centre price tags. Just real, legitimate training and real results.

We believe acting shouldn‚Äôt be locked behind London doors.
That‚Äôs why we‚Äôre bringing professional-level training to Yorkshire and the North, so anyone with the passion to perform can do it, whether you‚Äôre 16 or 60, starting fresh or chasing the dream you left behind.

üé≠ Because the truth is: there is no other independent studio in the UK that offers what we do.
We‚Äôre Spotlight approved.
We‚Äôre SAG recognised.
We make films.
We get results.

You don‚Äôt get more legitimate than that.
You just don‚Äôt.

So, if you‚Äôre ready to stop wondering ‚Äúwhat if‚Äù and start actually doing it, this is your moment.

üî• SPOTLIGHT APPROVED. SAG RECOGNISED. FILM FOCUSED.
The Foundry Acting Studio‚Ä¶.
Where impossible dreams get rehearsed, filmed, and released.

****üìç Location:** **HOME Mcr**, 2 Tony Wilson Pl, Manchester M15 4FN **

****üïë Time:** 2:00 p.m. - 6:30 p.m. **

Tickets are available at this link. 

[https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239](https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239)

Don‚Äôt miss out‚Äîmake sure to stop by and connect with her!

 

Come and join us, we can‚Äôt wait to meet you üåü

Project: FEATURE FILM - "End The Wait"

DATE NEEDED:

-we do NOT have exact Call/Wrap times, so you should have FULL day/night available to allow for whatever the Call/Wrap Times end up being. 

NON-UNION

_______________________________________________________
ROLES: **Featured TALENT**
[COURTROOM PARTICIPANTS] Male and Female, age range 21-70 years old, all ethnicities, wide variety of types, MUST have some type of IMPROV ability or be able to "make up" dialogue on the spot to create certain courtroom situations. items.text:
Mickey Mouse Horror Short Film
Hello, I am currently producing a Mickey Mouse Short film, with the working title, The Mouse Killer, which may become the actual title. 

This film is apart of my two existing films, My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh 1 and 2. This serves as the next chapter within the series, that will lead into the 3rd and final My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh film. 

Film Synopsis: two women are out in the woods, hunting down a mythical creature known as, Steamboat Willie, or Willie. 

If it all works out, this short film will be the start of a trilogy of short films. With the final one leading up to My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh 3.

Actors Age Range: 21 to up.

Looking for two females who can play the roles.

Compensation: none

Location: Fort Collins Colorado 

If you're interested, send me a message!

üé•** PAID CASTING CALL**

We are casting several roles for a series of short narrative pieces that highlight the stories of real families supported by our organization. These stories portray authenticity, warmth, and emotional depth.

**Location:** East Vancouver
**Audition Date:** October 20th

**Shooting Date:** October 23rd; must be available from 10-4 (you will not be needed the entire day)
**Compensation:** $200

**We are looking for actresses/actors to play: **

**Bruna**
* Female, late 20s to mid-40s
* Mother; caring and loving. Must convey determination, worry, and hope while navigating financial and emotional challenges for her children.

**Aisha**
* Female, early 30s to mid-40s
* Mother; warm, exhausted, and hopeful. Portrays a single parent managing multiple responsibilities with love and perseverance.

**Steven**
* Male, early 30s to mid-50s
* Father; provides care and guidance amid family hardship. Able to convey emotional strength and compassion.

**David**
* Male, mid-30s to 50s
* Father; supportive, patient, and empathetic. Represents the emotional toll of parenting through challenges while remaining steadfast for his family.

Please send a brief introduction and your headshot to **communications@ldsociety.ca. **We encourage applicants of all ethnicities and gender identities to apply.

Following auditions, we will confirm if you got the role and your timeslot via email on Tuesday, October 21st.

Calm, safe set with full health & safety protocols ‚Äî baby‚Äôs well-being is the top priority

If you have a baby basket or bassinet, let us know ‚Äî it may be used for the scene

üì£üé¨ CASTING CALL - Short Period Drama 

We are casting for The Stuntman, a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 10th November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:
Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. With his fianc√©e Alice by his side, Ed stages one last ambitious stunt in the hope of saving his cinema - and their livelihood. A warm yet bittersweet drama about determination, passion and the march of technological change.

Roles:
Ed Morris (Lead, 28)
Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but hiding a quiet desperation as he struggles to keep silent film alive. Needs strong screen presence and subtle emotional depth.

Alice Fardon (Lead, 22‚Äì23)
Ed‚Äôs fianc√©e. Feisty, loyal, and practical. She supports his dreams but occasionally shows frustration at his all-consuming determination.

Community Extras
Townsfolk gathering to watch Ed‚Äôs big stunt. A mix of ages. Families, workers and individuals. To capture the atmosphere of a 1920s local community.

Apply by: 1st November 2025
To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Please include in email subject: THE STUNTMAN & NAME

LOCATION: Denver Area, Colorado
SUBMISSION DEADLINE: Friday, October 24th

USAGE: Full buyout

ROLES AVAILABLE:

CHILD (Male, 7-10) - SPEAKING ROLE - $700/day
Lead role! Looking for a talented young actor who can deliver genuine Christmas morning excitement. Must submit reel showing previous work. This is a standout role perfect for your reel!

ADULT LANDLORD (Male, 45-55) - NON-SPEAKING - $350-400/day 

Plays grown-up version of Child. Warm, relatable, trustworthy presence. Reel or work samples required.

MOM (Female, 30-40) - NON-SPEAKING - $350-400/day
Supportive, amused mom in 1970s Christmas scene. Natural reactions, expressive warmth. Reel or work samples required.

DAD (Male, 30-40) - NON-SPEAKING - $350-400/day
Bemused but proud dad, possibly behind camera with VHS camcorder. Reel or work samples required.

-Meals provided on set

Have you ever wanted to be an actor, but people told you it was impossible?

Maybe you believed them.

The truth is, it is possible. And we‚Äôre proving it every single day.

At The Foundry Acting Studio, we‚Äôve taken people from call centres, factories, construction sites and put them on real film sets. We‚Äôve helped ordinary people create extraordinary careers.

Because when you train with us, you‚Äôre not just joining another acting class, you‚Äôre stepping into a professional studio that‚Äôs already earned the highest recognition possible:

‚ú® SPOTLIGHT APPROVED ‚Äì our curriculum exceeds the UK‚Äôs highest acting standard by over three times.

And all of this ‚Äî for just ¬£100 every 4 weeks (¬£80 for teens).
No false promises. No city centre price tags. Just real, legitimate training and real results.

We believe acting shouldn‚Äôt be locked behind London doors.
That‚Äôs why we‚Äôre bringing professional-level training to Yorkshire and the North, so anyone with the passion to perform can do it, whether you‚Äôre 16 or 60, starting fresh or chasing the dream you left behind.

üé≠ Because the truth is: there is no other independent studio in the UK that offers what we do.
We‚Äôre Spotlight approved.
We‚Äôre SAG recognised.
We make films.
We get results.

You don‚Äôt get more legitimate than that.
You just don‚Äôt.

So, if you‚Äôre ready to stop wondering ‚Äúwhat if‚Äù and start actually doing it, this is your moment.

üî• SPOTLIGHT APPROVED. SAG RECOGNISED. FILM FOCUSED.
The Foundry Acting Studio‚Ä¶.
Where impossible dreams get rehearsed, filmed, and released.
